            "description": "'...this is where surf music would be        if all the futuristic '60s predictions came true. This dark and mysterious         band sounds as if a very clean-cut and tattoo-free X cut the sound track         for an independent movie..... The difference between [the]N.U.R.B-S and         the earlier Ventures/Dick Dale/Beach Boys sound is the difference between         LA punk and Phil Spector pop -- it's darker, and reflective of a society         without optimism and struggling to get by. While things might get pretty bad,        dating and surfing are still options, but the beach is polluted and everyone         has an STD.' (Quoted from Carl F Gauze         http://www.ink19.com/issues/august2007/musicReviews/musicN/nurbs.html)",
            "name": "theN.U.R.B-S."
